An Optimization
An Optimization of E-Step in EM
The original formula for implementation

\displaystyle p_c = \frac{1}{\sqrt{\Pi_h^H 2\pi S_{ch}^2}}\exp^{-\sum_h^H\frac{(V_{ch}^{''}-M_{ch})^2}{2S_{ch}^2}}


\displaystyle r_c = \frac{a_c^{'}p_c}{\sum_j a_j^{'}p_j}

The optimized formula for implementation - built-in softmax, numerical stable

\begin{eqnarray}
\displaystyle q_c 
& = & \log(p_c) 
  =   \log\left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{\Pi_h^H 2\pi S_{ch}^2}}\exp^{-\sum_h^H\frac{(V_{ch}^{''}-M_{ch})^2}{2S_{ch}^2}}\right) \\
& = & -\sum_h^H\frac{(V_{ch}^{''}-M_{ch})^2}{2S_{ch}^2} - \sum_h^H\log(S_{ch}) - \frac{H}{2}\log(2\pi)
\end{eqnarray}

since -\frac{H}{2}\log(2\pi) is a constant as long as H is determined, let:

\displaystyle \widetilde{q}_c = -\sum_h^H\frac{(V_{ch}^{''}-M_{ch})^2}{2S_{ch}^2} - \sum_h^H\log(S_{ch}) 

therefore,

\begin{eqnarray}
\displaystyle r_c = \frac{a_c^{'}p_c}{\sum_j a_j^{'}p_j} 
& = & \frac{a_c^{'}\exp(\log(p_c))}{\sum_j a_j^{'}\exp(\log(p_j))} \\
& = & \frac{a_c^{'}\exp(q_c)}{\sum_j a_j^{'}\exp(q_j)} \\
& = & \frac{a_c^{'}\exp(\widetilde{q}_c)}{\sum_j a_j^{'}\exp(\widetilde{q}_j)} \\
& = & \text{softmax}(\boldsymbol{a\widetilde{q}}) \\
\end{eqnarray}
